{{Quote|It means that we will declare total war against our enemy, and not cease until he has been completely destroyed.|[[Admiral/Legends|Admiral]] [[Traest Kre'fey]]|<ref name="The New Jedi Order: Destiny's Way">''[[The New Jedi Order: Destiny's Way]]''</ref>}}
'''Ar'krai''' (also spelled '''ar'kai''') was a state of genocidal war among the [[Bothan/Legends|Bothans]]. The basic tenets of ar'krai state that if it was declared, all fit Bothans&mdash;and usually those that were not&mdash;were required to volunteer for military service against an enemy that threatened the Bothans with extinction&mdash;and the Bothans were to repay the enemy in kind. The enemy was to be destroyed to the last individual in an act of [[speciecide]], their name be wiped from [[Timeline of galactic history/Legends|history]], and their [[Homeworld/Legends|homeworld]] be ground to dust. In recorded Bothan history, ar'krai was declared only three times. The third was during the [[Yuuzhan Vong War]], after the [[Battle of Coruscant (Yuuzhan Vong War)|Battle of Coruscant]] and the sacrifice of the Bothan [[Borsk Fey'lya]], [[Chief of State (New Republic)/Legends|Chief of State]] of the [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]].

Ar'krai did not have a concept of ceasefire. Even [[40 ABY/Legends|ten years after]] the end of the war, Bothan fundamentalists were still attempting to locate [[Zonama Sekot/Legends|Zonama Sekot]] and destroy the [[Yuuzhan Vong]]. The [[Planet/Legends|planet]], however, remained safely hidden. Even into later years, the [[True Victory Party]] wished to carry out ar'krai and completely eradicate the Yuuzhan Vong.

